      <hedline>
        <hl1>Radio Interference</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Judy G Grastorf letter on July 20 article on electronic fences for dogs</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The electrified fence will not keep some other dog out of your yard. A stray dog (a 75-pound German shepherd mix) came into my yard two years ago and attacked my 25-pound cocker spaniel. My dog survived and recovered -- after surgery and 10 days on antibiotics. Now I have the backyard completely enclosed with standard fencing.</p>
        <p>JUDY G. GRASTORF  Orange, N.J.</p>
      </block>
